.TH "vga_tryget" 9 "vga_tryget" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
vga_tryget \- try to acquire & lock legacy VGA resources
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" vga_tryget
.BI "(struct pci_dev *pdev "  ","
.BI "unsigned int rsrc "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "pdev" 12
pci devivce of VGA card or NULL for system default
.IP "rsrc" 12
bit mask of resources to acquire and lock
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This function performs the same operation as \fBvga_get\fP, but will return an
error (-EBUSY) instead of blocking if the resources are already locked by
another card. It can be called in any context

On success, release the VGA resource again with \fBvga_put\fP.

0 on success, negative error code on failure.
.SH "RETURN"
